{"info": {"author": "cpuabuse.com", "author_email": "pypi@cpuabuse.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: ISC License (ISCL)", "Natural Language :: English", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules", "Typing :: Typed"], "description": "# absolute-import\n\n## About\n\nPackage providing a one-line functionality to set up a project for ability to perform absolute imports both after setup and with plain download. Additionally, provides namespaces support.\n\n## Usage\n\n### Absolute import\n\n1. In the root `__init__.py`.\n\n\t```python\n\tfrom absolute_import import absolute_import\n\n\tabsolute_import(file=__file__)\n\t```\n\n1. In the root `__main__.py` or root directly executable python files.\n\n\t```python\n\tfrom absolute_import import absolute_import\n\n\tif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n\t\tabsolute_import(file=__file__)\n\t```\n\n### Absolute import and namespace\n\n1. In the root `__init__.py`.\n\n\t```python\n\tfrom absolute_import import absolute_import\n\n\tabsolute_import(file=__file__, name=__name__, path=__path__)\n\t```\n\n1. In the root `__main__.py` or root directly executable python files.\n\n\t```python\n\tfrom absolute_import import absolute_import\n\n\tif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n\t\tabsolute_import(file=__file__, name=__name__, path=__path__)\n\t```", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/cpuabuse/absolute-import", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "absolute-import", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/absolute-import/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/absolute-import/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/cpuabuse/absolute-import"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/absolute-import/0.4/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": ">=3.6", "summary": "A package to automate setting up absolute imports and namespace.", "version": "0.4", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>absolute-import</h1>\n<h2>About</h2>\n<p>Package providing a one-line functionality to set up a project for ability to perform absolute imports both after setup and with plain download. Additionally, provides namespaces support.</p>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<h3>Absolute import</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>In the root <code>__init__.py</code>.</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">absolute_import</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">absolute_import</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">absolute_import</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"vm\">__file__</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>In the root <code>__main__.py</code> or root directly executable python files.</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">absolute_import</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">absolute_import</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"vm\">__name__</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"__main__\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n\t<span class=\"n\">absolute_import</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"vm\">__file__</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Absolute import and namespace</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>In the root <code>__init__.py</code>.</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">absolute_import</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">absolute_import</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">absolute_import</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"vm\">__file__</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"vm\">__name__</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">path</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">__path__</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>In the root <code>__main__.py</code> or root directly executable python files.</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">absolute_import</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">absolute_import</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"vm\">__name__</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"__main__\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n\t<span class=\"n\">absolute_import</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"vm\">__file__</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"vm\">__name__</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">path</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">__path__</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n</li>\n</ol>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6685697, "releases": {"0.0.dev1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "1f1f0712dc743051313bbd809de9623b", "sha256": "a3ef5b1593b6fc2c49c472a4e4a26d9f03929ffd10acdb8252c55b9ddd3ba951"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "absolute-import-0.0.dev1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "1f1f0712dc743051313bbd809de9623b", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.3", "size": 2116, "upload_time": "2020-02-21T06:28:23", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-21T06:28:23.592989Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/4a/f5/ee018e55ca32690e945a69a381279a96fdf57d2c19a23d91c547dcc2c3bf/absolute-import-0.0.dev1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.3": [